INTERMINE

These Perl modules allow the creation of file in InterMine XML format, 
as well as directly querying the web API.

SEE ALSO

http://trac.flymine.org/wiki/ItemsAPIPerl

perldoc lib/InterMine/ItemFactory.pm

INSTALLATION

(You can use the web service sample scripts without installing these modules.
Please see documentation below)

To install this module, run the following commands 1 - 3:

1) To make:
    cpan -i XML::Parser::PerlSAX XML::Writer IO::String URI LWP::UserAgent Text::CSV_XS
    perl Makefile.PL
    make

2) To run the tests: (optional)
    cpan -i Test::XML Test::More Test::Exception Test::MockObject Test::Warn
    make test

3) To install:
    make install

Don't forget to use elevated permissions (eg sudo) for cpan and step 3.

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for these modules with 
the perldoc command.

Please read the sample scripts under samples/FlyMine and samples/modMine
to see ways in which you can use this interface - there are examples for
queries to the webservice and using these modules to call the API. Installation
of these modules is not necessary to use the webservice examples.

support@flymine.org

